Write a program that randomly selects a list of 20 integers from 1 to 100 and analyzes them. The program should:
• prompt the user for an operation to perform on the randomly selected numbers: calculate the average of the numbers, find the maximum and minimum, sort the numbers in ascending or descending order, and display even and odd numbers,
• handle exceptions, e.g., when the user enters an invalid option or range of numbers,
• display the results in a readable form on the console,
• save the results to a text file,
• allow for repeating operations without restarting the program

